properties.areaDesc: Two Rivers to Sheboygan WI; Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI; Sturgeon Bay to Two Rivers WI
properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 10 at 3:40AM CST until January 12 at 2:00AM CST by NWS Green Bay WI
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Small Craft Advisory, waves 2 to 5 ft. For the
Gale Watch, northeast winds 20 to 30 kt with gusts up to 40 kt
and waves 7 to 12 ft possible.

* WHERE...Rock Island Passage to Sturgeon Bay WI, Sturgeon Bay
to Two Rivers WI and Two Rivers to Sheboygan WI.

* WHEN...For the Small Craft Advisory, until 8 AM CST this
morning. For the Gale Watch, from Saturday morning through
late Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds can cause hazardous waves which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should consider altering plans to avoid possible
hazardous conditions.  Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter
course, and/or secure the vessel for severe wind and waves.

NWSheadline: SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 AM CST THIS MORNING... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SATURDAY MORNING THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
